manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Closer to Natural Breastfeeding! Simulates same suck, swallow and breathe patterns as breastfeeding As baby feeds, the soft disposable liner inside the bottle gently collapses (like the breast does naturally when breastfeeding) to prevent air from mixing with the milk and getting into baby’s tummy. This air-free feeding helps to reduce colic. Helps Baby Latch On Naturally The Most Like Mom NaturaLatch Nipple has a natural wide shape and a raised texture which helps baby latch on naturally. Easy Switching Between Breast and Bottle Feeding Clinically proven to allow for a more natural feeding rhythm and promotes easy switching between breast and bottle feeding.

More Natural Breathing -- Clinically Proven -- Pre-sterilized liner gently collapses like Mom’s breast as baby feeds. -- Baby sucks and swallows in a coordinated rhythm that mimics natural breastfeeding, so baby breathes more naturally during feeding! Easy Switching Between Breast and Bottle -- Most like Mom Naturalatch Nipple has a raised texture area that helps baby latch on naturally. Mimics baby’s latch-on like the breast for easy natural feeding. -- Promotes proper latch-on for easy switching between breast and bottle. Air-Free Feeding to Help Reduce Colic -- Unique anti-colic liner gently collapses as baby feeds, preventing air bubbles from mixing with milk and getting into baby’s tummy. Less air bubbles means less gas, colic and discomfort.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love these!!
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely love these bottle liners! I prefer these bottle over plastic bottles for sure! These are so convenient because you just replace a new one each time. I don’t know why I can’t find these in any of my local stores but I prefer these over any other bottles I have used. Well these or glass bottles. But if you don’t want to go the glass bottle route then I would definitely recommend bottles with liners.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Value and Great Product
reviews.reviewText: The drop-ins are fitted for playtex bottles; they work with the nurser and the venti air (just take unscrew the bottom). I got these as an add-on item and they were around $4 compared to the $7 you will pay at Walmart. They are very convenient to have around the house or to take on trips. If you are like me and are old school these bottles are very easy to warm up in the sink. I would highly recommend these to parents and family and friends who are wondering what to buy mom-to-be.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 20, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Have bought thousands, and still pleased
reviews.reviewText: Update: We are again using these liners in our Playtex bottles for our new baby. She is 12 weeks old, and I am still very pleased with them. No leaks, easy clean up, easy bottle filling. I like being able to get them on Subscribe & Save. We go through 8 liners/day, so a box of 100 lasts just under 2 weeks.Original review:I've been using these liners in bottles since shortly after my baby was born. We had nursing difficulty, and after several consultations with lactation, moved to exclusive pumping by about six weeks of age.I chose this type of bottle because it was what I remembered from my youth and babysitting days. (I had someone comment to me that these were so "old fashioned", as though that was a reason she wouldn't use them.) I love being able to get the air out of the bottle, and how the bag collapses as the baby feeds.I went into my order history, and I have bought 2400 bags (24 boxes) in recent months (plus a box I bought at a big box stores waiting on one shipment) almost entirely through subscribe & save. I have only had two bags that had any sort of defect. They we're sort of crunched up at the top of the box (perhaps due to the way they were packed in there) and the top wouldn't lay flat against the rim.I've never had a leak that wasn't my fault (a couple of times I didn't get the lid screwed on tight...user error).I like knowing that I have a clean start to each bottle -- really cuts down on bottle washing time (especially since we don't have a dishwasher).I have no issues, and would use these again for a future child.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 21, 2014
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So easy to use
reviews.reviewText: We have twins so when purchasing products, it was all about investing money in things that would make our lives simpler. These Drop-Ins work really well for the bottles. The bag collapses as they consume the contents, which supposedly improves problems with gas but I'm not sure this system accomplishes it better than any others. Because the bag is thin, it also takes a lot less time to warm bottles if that is a consideration. The real savings is the manpower and time necessary for cleaning. I only have 4 bottles per baby, replace the liner and nipple when necessary, and wash everything once a day. These don't come cheap so I don't think there is any cost savings associated with this versus buying a boat load of bottles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2011
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Baby and we love it!
reviews.reviewText: Great thoughtful design. One of those things make early motherhood easy.I wish I started using them earlier. My baby had nipple confusion using other brands and it took a long time to lure him back to the breasts. With Playtex slow flow nipples baby is switch between breasts and bottles easily now.It so easy for me - easy to clean (only the nipple and the ring), easy to setup (drop in), formula can be mixed in the bottle with drop-in directly. Very light and easy to pack extras for long trip.My baby loves it!! It collapses so baby hardly suck in air; It's light weight with an open bottomed holder. My baby was able to be able to hold the bottle by the holder at feeding since 3 months old and loves the involvement.All in all to me it represents great product design - simple concept, well executed, with many benefits, and pleasant to senses. Good job!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best bottle system ever!!
reviews.reviewText: The playtex drop-in system is the only system I will use for my babies! When I first started using them with my first baby I immediately noticed so much less spit-up! I was so happy that I’ll likely never use another system again. So worth it. Don’t have to even clean out bottles all day. And I save on having to buy expensive bottles and racks. Super cost effective.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2014
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Convenient, Clean up is a breeze, but not eco friendly.
reviews.reviewText: Some people say that these drop-ins did not keep a good seal, but I found that those individuals were trying to push all the air out through the nipple and the pressure is what broke the seal. If you want less air just press some of the air out before putting the ring on. Pressing all the air out is unnecessary. The liner does its job without pressing all the air out. The point of the collapsible liner is to not let more air in as your baby eats, and it does a fantastic job. If you would rather not buy replacement liners, Playtex VentAire takes the same nipples and does the same job with a vent at the bottom, keeping a seal when the pressure of the milk is on it, and then allowing air in through the bottom to replace the milk as the baby eats. These don't leak as long as the bottom ring is screwed on properly. I loved them because I didn't have to buy replacements and it did the same job!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 17, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Product - No problems with holes mentioned in other reviews.
reviews.reviewText: We've been using these and absolutely love them! So much easier to clean than other bottle systems. Can easily remove all air to improve gassiness and colic in little one. Just press in the liner from the bottom. We are currently supplementing with formula and only using 2oz per feeding in a 4 oz liner, and it is still easy to remove the air.With the ring and nipple loosely on the bottle we carefully press on the liner from the bottom until the liquid level nears the top of the liner. Then we tighten the lid and continue to press any remaining air out through the hole in the nipple (be careful when pushing up on the liner before tightening the lid as liquid can easily overflow). If your fingers are not long enough, we sometimes use the handles of some of our kitchen serving utensils to aid in removing the air.

Love the liner because it allows me to have a clean bottle during the night feedings without having to run to the kitchen sink downstairs to wash. Also, the thin liner allows me to warm up the milk just using hot tap water in the washroom making it so quick and easy

These are excellent, you just fit them into the bottle, fill to the line, screw on the cap, and press out the air. My baby loves drinking from these bottles with the bags and we've noticed a decrease in the amount of air he swallows while feeding. p.s. got the idea based on what I remembered from my childhood, seeing my mother use these bags with bottles for my younger siblings. Glad the product has lasted.
Takes time to come but no problems with it so far been through a couple boxes already and no leaks, on the cheaper side than same options on here
Not eco-friendly but easy to use and don't worry about cleanliness
